To finish with we then looked at IP Troubleshooting which in order to start this you must check if the computer/machine you are using has TCP/IP enabled as this is important. In order to check if the computer itself has an IP assigned to it you can either use ipconfig for windows and ifconfig for mac. This will display details about the computer as well as the IP you are looking for. To check if it is working you can then use a PING which sends a small packet to a particular IP address in order to check if the network connections are intact. After this you can perform a DIG command which essential performs a DNS(Domain Name System) as another check for whether or not it is properly connected to the network. You can also TRACE ROUTE to see if the network and the intended destination are making the correct connection.\
\
Remote access protocols are used to control the establishment of connections and the transmission of data over WAN links. A public key infrastructure is a set of roles, policies and procedures needed to create, manage and distribute use, store and revoke digital certificates and manage public key encryption. \cf3 \cb4 The purpose of a PKI is to facilitate the secure electronic transfer of information for a range of network activities such as e-commerce, internet banking and confidential email. It is required for activities where simple passwords are an inadequate authentication method and more rigorous proof is required to confirm the identity of the parties involved in the communication and to validate the information being transferred. A Bring Your Own Device Policy (BYOD) essentially allows employees to bring their own devices to their places under certain levels of permission. There must be a strict policy put towards what devices are actually permitted as certain software used by the company may only certain certain types of phones/laptops/pcs. The user must agree to then establish certain levels of security on their device so that if it is lost or stolen anyone can not access vital information about the company. Another policy to implement along with the BYOD policy would be an acceptable use policy which decides what apps can be used and what websites can be accessed under this policy. It also will allow the company to monitor the user to ensure that maximum work effort is being achieved. Finally a very important point to remember is what to do whenever the employee exits the company and how the levels of access and authority will be removed from any devices that they have set up.\
