We next looked at how we would troubleshoot problems when it came to different types of connection to the internet. The connections we looked at were cable and ASDL connection. The best way to diagnose and fix your internet connection is simply to turn it off for 10 seconds and then turn it back on again. Most of the time this fix will work but if it doesn\'92t then you may need to look at more in depth fixes to work out the problem. After this you should follow all your connections back to make sure the correct cables are connected in the correct holes. For example your ADSL connection has not come loose or even the power cable is sitting loose. You should then perform a DNS check which tells you whether it is a problem with your internet or a problem with whatever you are trying to connect to online. If the problem stills persists then you may have to connect your internet provider and make arrangements for the problem to be fixed by them. \
