After this we learned about the steps that need to be taken in order to make sure that a computer will remain functional and in the future not come to a full system failure. It is imperative that all updates for the OS, the security software and any other programs are installed. Updates bring patches that allow the security of the system to constantly maintained so hard drives etc cannot be infected and ruined over time. After all these have been done it is important to make sure that the insides of your computer are properly cleaned using either compressed air or if the situation is very bad a selection of anti static cleaning wipes and solutions. Dust can lie on fans and prevent them from working to maximum effectiveness which over time will cause your computer to work harder and overheat. After this we then discussed why a hard drive should be partitioned and formatted and what is the main reasoning behind this. Disk partitioning is separating one physical hard drive into multiple independent volumes. \cf5 \cb1 Disk partitioning or disk slicing is the creation of one or more regions on a hard disk or other secondary storage, so that an operating system can manage information in each region separately. Partitioning is typically the first of preparing a newly manufactured disk before any files or directories have been created. For example if we you were to install a new operating system such as ubuntu it would be necessary to partition and format the hard drive as it will be a fresh new start. Disk formatting is basically the second part of the process, making the data storage deice visible to an operating system.\
